body:
The following example, based on sv-tests's sv-tests/third_party/tools/icarus/ivtest/ivltests/pr1883052b.v , hangs.

I'd be ok if it was due to Verilator's having all combo-sensitivities always activating, and adding a `$finish` solving it, but that doesn't help.  It's hanging in `V3Sched.cpp`'s injection of a while() loop.

Maybe @kbieganski you can advise?

```
// verilog_format: off
`define stop $stop
`define checkh(gotv,expv) do if ((gotv) !== (expv)) begin $write("%%Error: %s:%0d:  got='h%x exp='h%x\n", `__FILE__,`__LINE__, (gotv), (expv)); `stop; end while(0);
// verilog_format: on

module t;
  reg [3:0] ia = 4'd1;
  wire signed [3:0] iconstm, isfunc, iufunc;

  // verilator lint_off WIDTH
  assign #1 iconstm = -2;  // -2

  assign #1 isfunc = $rtoi(2.0);  // 2

  assign #1 iufunc = int_func(ia);  // 2
  // verilator lint_on WIDTH

  initial begin
    #1;
    `checkh(iconstm, 4'bx);
    `checkh(isfunc, 4'bx);
    `checkh(iufunc, 4'bx);

    #1;
    `checkh(iconstm, -2);
    `checkh(isfunc, 2);
    `checkh(iufunc, 2);

    $finish;  // FIXME not in original test
  end

  function [31:0] int_func;
    input [31:0] in;
    int_func = in * 2;
  endfunction

endmodule
```

